      "message": "Allows Maven to do String -\u003e enum conversion. Maven accepts spellings like\n\n  true,\n  TRUE\n  TruE\n\n(just like it would for @Parameters of type boolean), but throws a MojoConfigurationException on illegal values like \"unknown\".\n\nFWIW, I think Tycho\u0027s code could benefit from this pattern generally; sometimes you use plain Strings (\"consider\" for pomDependencies), so that the user doesn\u0027t get MojoConfigurationExceptions if entering an illegal value. At other times, you use *lowercase* enum constants, which not only look odd in Java code, but also prevent the user from using a different spelling (which Maven allows for booleans, for example), although you can rightly argue that being strict about the spelling is a good thing, of course.",
