      "message": "This is the second time [1] that we get a proposal to use the incorrect toUpperCase() method to make configuration case-insensitive. (Correct would have been toUpperCase(Locale.ENGLISH))\n\nSo trying to implement case-insensitive configuration support is error-prone. Therefore, I\u0027m -1 on generally making the configuration case-insensitive.\n\nYou are right about the case-insensitive support for \"true\" (which is implemented as Boolean.valueOf(String)). Still, I wouldn\u0027t spend any effort on this because there is no use case as far as I know. The fact that this is then inconsistent is a hint that maybe we shouldn\u0027t use \"true\"... \n\nIf you don\u0027t like the lower-case enum values, I\u0027d propose to store the expected configuration strings in the enum constants, e.g.\n\n EMPTY(\"empty\")\n\nand implement an own String -\u003e Enum conversion method.\n\n[1] https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/32331/6/tycho-core/src/main/java/org/eclipse/tycho/core/resolver/DefaultTargetPlatformConfigurationReader.java",
